'''Black Saturday''' was a particularly dark, stormy Saturday in Scotland, on 4 August 1621. Many regarded the foul weather as a judgment of [[Heaven]] against Acts then passed<ref>[http://thereformation.info/articles_of_perth.htm The Articles of Perth]</ref> in the [[Parliament of Scotland|Scots Parliament]] tending to establish [[Episcopacy]].<ref>[http://www.fullbooks.com/The-Nuttall-Encyclopaedia7.html The-Nuttall-Encyclopaedia]</ref>
Many suicides were recorded on this day, as some saw the foul weather as a preparatory for [[Armageddon]].<ref>[http://www.undiscoveredscotland.co.uk/usebooks/lang-shorthistory/section15.html ''A Short History of Scotland''], Andrew Lang</ref>
